description:
Create the ChatProvider trait abstraction for pluggable backend support.

**New Module:** crates/forge-chat/src/provider.rs

**Core Trait:**
```rust
#[async_trait]
pub trait ChatProvider: Send + Sync {
    /// Process a chat command with context and tools
    async fn process(
        &self, 
        prompt: &str, 
        context: &DashboardContext,
        tools: &[ToolDefinition]
    ) -> Result<ProviderResponse>;

    /// Provider name for logging/debugging
    fn name(&self) -> &str;

    /// Whether provider supports streaming responses
    fn supports_streaming(&self) -> bool { false }

    /// Estimated cost per request (if known)
    fn estimated_cost(&self) -> Option<f64> { None }
}
```

**ProviderResponse:**
```rust
pub struct ProviderResponse {
    pub text: String,
    pub tool_calls: Vec<ToolCall>,
    pub finish_reason: FinishReason,
    pub usage: Option<TokenUsage>,
}

pub enum FinishReason {
    Stop,
    ToolCall,
    MaxTokens,
    Error(String),
}

pub struct TokenUsage {
    pub input_tokens: u32,
    pub output_tokens: u32,
    pub cache_read_tokens: u32,
    pub cache_creation_tokens: u32,
}
```

**Factory Pattern:**
```rust
pub fn create_provider(config: &ProviderConfig) -> Result<Box<dyn ChatProvider>> {
    match config.provider_type {
        ProviderType::ClaudeCli => Ok(Box::new(ClaudeCliProvider::new(config)?)),
        ProviderType::ClaudeApi => Ok(Box::new(ClaudeApiProvider::new(config)?)),
    }
}
```

